Package com.android

Class Fireman<T>

java.lang.Object
com.android.Fireman<T>
Type Parameters:
T - this is the type that will be supplied when creating a Fireman and will apply to the generic type of the UnaryOperator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Function<T,​T>, UnaryOperator<T>
public class Fireman<T>
extends Object
implements UnaryOperator<T>
class Fireman implements the UnaryOperator interface, so it has to provide implementation for the apply method of the UnaryOperator interface. when we create an Fireman Fireman<Integerl>myFireman=new Fireman<Integer>() we are setting type T to be an Integer which means the UnaryOperator type T will also be a Integer
